  "body": "Hey,\r\n\r\nThe main Geth documentation indicates that this should be possible, but couldn't figure it out.\r\n\r\nI'm trying to \"simulate\" a call that requires token balance to be positive, otherwise reverts. Assumably I could do this by either changing contract's balance[account] mapping or overriding balanceOf function.\r\n\r\nCould anyone guide how the eth_call's \"State override set\" should be formulated for this kind of action?\r\n\r\nThank_s !\r\n\r\nDAMN I'm blind!\r\n\r\nThere's an override example on the documentation's bottom section.\r\n\r\nAnyway, still, can I assume that state override set should be formulated like this:\r\n{\r\n    Contract address: { code: bytecode from compiler }\r\n}\r\n\r\nNow does the bytecode need to be full contract code? Or can I just inject partial code, for example just defining the override function or mapping?\r\n\r\nThanks",
